    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "=define",
        "text": "=Analyze the attached receipt image and extract structured data.\n\n  IMPORTANT: The total amount is usually prominently displayed. Pay special       \n  attention to the final amount that was actually paid.\n                                                                                  \n  1. RECEIPT_INFO:     \n     - Always output dates in ISO format (YYYY-MM-DD).\n     - Store name (normalized: REWE, IKEA, ESSO, etc.)                            \n     - Currency (EUR, USD, etc.)\n     - Total amount (the actual amount paid)                                      \n     - Tax amount (if recognizable, otherwise 0)\n     - Subtotal (if printed on the receipt; if not, calculate it as the sum of all\n   item prices)                                                                   \n     - Deposits (Pfand): sum of all deposit charges if present, otherwise 0\n     - Discounts: sum of all discounts or coupons if present, otherwise 0         \n                                                                                  \n  2. INDIVIDUAL ITEMS:                                                            \n     - For each item: name, category, price, quantity                             \n     - Use specific categories in singular English (Food, Beverage, Household,\n  Furniture, etc.)                                                                \n     - If quantity is not specified, assume 1\n     - For items sold by weight: include only the final price paid (e.g., \"Bananas\n   (by weight)\" with the actual paid amount)                                      \n     - Do not include reference prices (per-kilogram) as separate items if a total\n   price for that item also appears                                               \n     - If both per-unit and total price for the same item appear, use only the\n  total\n     - Do not include deposit charges or discounts as items\n     - Translate item names to English if not already in English\n  \n  3. CONFIDENCE SCORE:\n       - Rate your overall confidence in the extraction on a scale of 1 to 5\n       - 5 = all values clearly readable, high certainty\n       - 4 = mostly readable, minor ambiguities\n       - 3 = some values ambiguous (faded print, partial occlusion, unclear\n  handwriting)\n       - 2 = significant parts unclear, multiple guesses made\n       - 1 = image barely readable, extraction largely guesswork                                                                                \n  Return the result as JSON matching the provided schema.",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "type": "HumanMessagePromptTemplate",
              "messageType": "imageBinary",
              "imageDetail": "high"
            }
          ]
        },
        "batching": {}
      },
